Ann Cuerton Davies (born 25 November 1934, London) is an English actress. She was the wife of actor Richard Briers until his death in February 2013, and the mother of actress Lucy Briers and Katie Briers.
One of her earliest television appearances was as the character Jenny in the BBC series "Doctor Who" in the story entitled "The Dalek Invasion of Earth". In 2003 Davies appeared in a 2003 episode of the series "Doctors" as the character Annette Ludlow.
